SIMPLE: craziness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Craziness
<hw>Cra"zi*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being
broken down or weakened; <as>as, the <ex>craziness</ex> of a ship, or of
the limbs</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being broken in mind; imbecility or
weakness of intellect; derangement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crazing</ent>⟦br⟧
